which has the same double geometric sum structure as (7).

### Key Lemmas

**Lemma 2**.: _For all \(T\geq 1\), we have_

\[\sum_{t=0}^{T-1}\lVert z_{t}-x_{t}\rVert^{2}\leq\frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta )^{2}M}T\sigma^{2}+\frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta)^{2}}\sum_{t=0}^{T-1} \mathbb{E}\left\lVert\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\nabla f_{m}(x_{t}^{m})\right\rVert ^{2}. \tag{6}\]

Proof.: Since \(u_{-1}=0\), unrolling the update rule of momentum, for any \(t\geq 0\) we get

\[u_{t}=\beta u_{t-1}+(1-\beta)g_{t}=(1-\beta)\sum_{\tau=0}^{t}\beta^{t-\tau}g^{ \tau}.\]

Using this and the definition of the average iterates, we have

\[z_{t}-x_{t}=\frac{\beta}{1-\beta}(x_{t}-x_{t-1})=-\frac{\beta\eta}{1-\beta}u_{ t}=-\beta\eta\sum_{\tau=0}^{t}\beta^{t-\tau}g_{\tau}.\]

Using convexity of squared norm function and letting \(s_{t}\stackrel{{\text{def}}}{{=}}\sum_{\tau=0}^{t}\beta^{t-\tau} =\frac{1-\beta^{t+1}}{1-\beta}\), for all \(t\geq 0\), we have

\[\lVert z_{t}-x_{t}\rVert^{2}=\eta^{2}\beta^{2}s_{t}^{2}\left\lVert\sum_{\tau=0 }^{t}\frac{\beta^{t-\tau}}{s_{t}}g_{\tau}\right\rVert^{2}\leq\eta^{2}\beta^{2} s_{t}^{2}\sum_{\tau=0}^{t}\frac{\beta^{t-\tau}}{s_{t}}\lVert g_{\tau}\rVert^{2} \leq\frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{1-\beta}\sum_{\tau=0}^{t}\beta^{t-\tau}\lVert g_ {\tau}\rVert^{2}.\]

Summing over the iterates yields

\[\sum_{t=0}^{T-1}\mathbb{E}\lVert z_{t}-x_{t}\rVert^{2} \leq \frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{1-\beta}\sum_{t=0}^{T-1}\sum_{\tau=0}^{t }\beta^{t-\tau}\mathbb{E}\lVert g_{\tau}\rVert^{2}\] \[= \frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{1-\beta}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1}\sum_{t=\tau} ^{T-1}\beta^{t-\tau}\mathbb{E}\lVert g_{\tau}\rVert^{2}\] \[= \frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{1-\beta}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1}\frac{1-\beta ^{T-\tau}}{1-\beta}\mathbb{E}\lVert g_{\tau}\rVert^{2}\] \[\leq \frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta)^{2}}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1}\mathbb{ E}\lVert g_{\tau}\rVert^{2}\] \[= \frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta)^{2}}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1}\mathbb{ E}\left\lVert\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}g_{\tau}^{m}-\nabla f_{m}(x_{\tau}^{m}) \right\rVert^{2}+\frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta)^{2}}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1} \mathbb{E}\left\lVert\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\nabla f_{m}(x_{\tau}^{m}) \right\rVert^{2}\] \[= \frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta)^{2}M^{2}}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1} \sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\left\lVert g_{\tau}^{m}-\nabla f_{m}(x_{\tau}^{m}) \right\rVert^{2}+\frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta)^{2}}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1} \mathbb{E}\left\lVert\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\nabla f_{m}(x_{\tau}^{m}) \right\rVert^{2}\] \[= \frac{\eta^{2}\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta)^{2}M}T\sigma^{2}+\frac{\eta^{2 }\beta^{2}}{(1-\beta)^{2}}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1}\mathbb{E}\left\lVert\frac{1}{M} \sum_{m=1}^{M}\nabla f_{m}(x_{\tau}^{m})\right\rVert^{2}.\]

**Lemma 3**.: _If \(24\eta^{2}L^{2}\psi\leq 1\), then_

\[\frac{1}{MT}\sum_{t=0}^{T-1}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\lVert x_{t}-x_{t}^{m} \rVert^{2}\leq 12\eta^{2}(B^{2}-1)\psi\cdot\frac{1}{T}\sum_{t=0}^{T-1} \mathbb{E}\lVert\nabla f(x_{t})\rVert^{2}+4\eta^{2}\psi(\sigma^{2}+3G^{2}),\]

_where_

\[\psi=\frac{4(1-p_{x})}{p_{x}^{2}}\cdot\frac{(1-\beta)(1-p_{u})}{1-(1-p_{u})\beta}\]Proof.: Let us expand the term \(\mathbb{E}\|x_{t+1}-x_{t+1}^{m}\|^{2}\) using \(x_{t+1}^{m}\)'s probabilistic update rule:

\[\mathbb{E}\|x_{t+1}-x_{t+1}^{m}\|^{2} = p_{x}\cdot 0+(1-p_{x})\cdot\mathbb{E}\|x_{t}-\eta u_{t}-(x_{t}^{m}- \eta u_{t}^{m})\|^{2}\] \[= (1-p_{x})\cdot\mathbb{E}\|x_{t}-x_{t}^{m}-\eta(u^{t}-u_{t}^{m})\| ^{2}\] \[\leq (1-p_{x})(1+s)\mathbb{E}\|x_{t}-x_{t}^{m}\|^{2}+\eta^{2}(1-p_{x}) (1+\sfrac{1}{/s})\mathbb{E}\|u_{t}-u_{t}^{m}\|^{2}\] \[\leq \eta^{2}(1-p_{x})(1+\sfrac{1}{/s})\sum_{\tau=1}^{t}((1-p_{x})(1+s ))^{t-\tau}\mathbb{E}\|u_{\tau}-u_{\tau}^{m}\|^{2}.\]

where \(s>0\) will be chosen later. Next we expand the term \(\mathbb{E}\|u_{t}-u_{t}^{m}\|^{2}\) using \(u_{t}^{m}\)'s probabilistic update rule:

\[\mathbb{E}\|u_{t}-u_{t}^{m}\|^{2} = p_{u}\cdot 0+(1-p_{u})\cdot\mathbb{E}\Bigg{\|}\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1 }^{M}(\beta u_{t-1}^{m}+(1-\beta)g_{t-1}^{m})-(\beta u_{t-1}^{m}+(1-\beta)g_{t- 1}^{m})\Bigg{\|}^{2}\] \[= (1-p_{u})\mathbb{E}\big{\|}\beta(u_{t-1}-u_{t-1}^{m})+(1-\beta)(g_ {t-1}-g_{t-1}^{m})\big{\|}^{2}\] \[\leq (1-p_{u})\beta\mathbb{E}\|(u_{t-1}-u_{t-1}^{m})\|^{2}+(1-p_{u})(1 -\beta)\mathbb{E}\|g_{t-1}-g_{t-1}^{m}\|^{2}\] \[\leq (1-p_{u})(1-\beta)\sum_{\tau=0}^{t-1}((1-p_{u})\beta)^{t-1-\tau} \mathbb{E}\|g_{\tau}-g_{\tau}^{m}\|^{2}\] \[\leq \frac{1-\beta}{\beta}\sum_{\tau=0}^{t-1}((1-p_{u})\beta)^{t-\tau} \mathbb{E}\|g_{\tau}-g_{\tau}^{m}\|^{2}\]

Denote \(q_{1}=(1-p_{x})(1+s)\) and \(q_{2}=(1-p_{u})\beta\). Combining the previous two bounds, we get

\[\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|x_{t}-x_{t}^{m}\|^{2}\] \[\leq \eta^{2}(1-p_{x})(1+\sfrac{1}{/s})\sum_{\tau=1}^{t}((1-p)(1+s))^{ t-\tau}\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|u_{\tau}-u_{\tau}^{m}\|^{2}\] \[\leq \eta^{2}(1-p_{x})(1+\sfrac{1}{/s})\sum_{\tau=1}^{t}((1-p_{u})(1+s ))^{t-\tau}\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\Bigg{[}\frac{1-\beta}{\beta}\sum_{\nu=0}^ {\tau-1}((1-p_{u})\beta)^{\tau-\nu}\mathbb{E}\|g_{\nu}-g_{\nu}^{m}\|^{2}\Bigg{]}\] \[= \eta^{2}(1-p_{x})(1+\sfrac{1}{/s})\frac{1-\beta}{\beta}\sum_{\tau =1}^{t}\sum_{\nu=0}^{\tau-1}q_{1}^{t-\tau}q_{2}^{t-\nu}\Bigg{[}\frac{1}{M}\sum _{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|g_{\nu}-g_{\nu}^{m}\|^{2}\Bigg{]}\] \[= \eta^{2}(1-p_{x})(1+\sfrac{1}{/s})\frac{1-\beta}{\beta}\sum_{\nu =0}^{t-1}\sum_{\nu=0}^{t}q_{1}^{t-\tau}q_{2}^{t-\nu}\Bigg{[}\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m =1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|g_{\nu}-g_{\nu}^{m}\|^{2}\Bigg{]}\] \[= \eta^{2}(1-p_{x})(1+\sfrac{1}{/s})\frac{1-\beta}{\beta}\sum_{\nu =0}^{t-1}q_{2}\frac{q_{1}^{t-\nu}-q_{2}^{t-\nu}}{q_{1}-q_{2}}\Bigg{[}\frac{1}{ M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|g_{\nu}-g_{\nu}^{m}\|^{2}\Bigg{]}\,,\] \[= \eta^{2}\underbrace{(1-p_{x})(1+\sfrac{1}{/s})(1-\beta)(1-p_{u}) }_{\stackrel{{\mbox{\tiny def}}}{{=}}\phi}\sum_{\nu=0}^{t-1}\frac {q_{1}^{t-\nu}-q_{2}^{t-\nu}}{q_{1}-q_{2}}\Bigg{[}\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M} \mathbb{E}\|g_{\nu}-g_{\nu}^{m}\|^{2}\Bigg{]}\,.\]Next, we bound the gradient term above.

\[\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|g_{t}^{m}-g_{t}\|^{2} = \frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\bigg{\|}g_{t}^{m}-\frac{1}{M} \sum_{i=1}^{K}g_{i}^{t}\bigg{\|}^{2}\] \[\leq \frac{2}{K}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\bigg{\|}g_{t}^{m}-\nabla f_{m} (x_{t}^{m})-\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}(g_{t}^{m}-\nabla f_{m}(x_{t}^{m}))\bigg{\|} ^{2}\] \[\quad+\frac{2}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\bigg{\|}\nabla f_{m}(x_{t }^{m})-\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\nabla f_{m}(x_{t}^{m})\bigg{\|}^{2}\] \[\text{(Lemma 4)} \leq \frac{2}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|g_{t}^{m}-\nabla f_{m}(x_{t} ^{m})\|^{2}-2\mathbb{E}\bigg{\|}\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}(g_{t}^{m}-\nabla f_{m }(x_{t}^{m}))\bigg{\|}^{2}\] \[\quad+\frac{12L^{2}}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|x_{t}-x_{t}^{m} \|^{2}+6(B^{2}-1)\mathbb{E}\|\nabla f(x_{t})\|^{2}+6G^{2}\] \[\leq 2\sigma^{2}+\frac{12L^{2}}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|x_{t}-x_{ t}^{m}\|^{2}+6(B^{2}-1)\mathbb{E}\|\nabla f(x_{t})\|^{2}+6G^{2}.\]

Again, plugging this bound to the previous one, we get

\[\frac{1}{MT}\sum_{t=0}^{T-1}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|x_{t}-x_{t}^ {m}\|^{2}\] \[\leq \frac{1}{MT}\sum_{t=1}^{T}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|x_{t}-x_{t}^{ m}\|^{2}\] \[\leq \frac{\eta^{2}\phi}{T}\sum_{t=1}^{T}\sum_{r=0}^{t-1}\frac{q_{1}^{ 1-\tau}-q_{2}^{1-\tau}}{q_{1}-q_{2}}\left[\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E} \|g_{\tau}-g_{r}^{m}\|^{2}\right]\] \[= \frac{\eta^{2}\phi}{T}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1}\frac{1}{q_{1}-q_{2}} \left(\frac{q_{1}(1-q_{1}^{T-\tau})}{1-q_{1}}-\frac{q_{2}(1-q_{2}^{T-\tau})}{1 -q_{2}}\right)\left[\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|g_{\tau}-g_{\tau}^{m }\|^{2}\right]\] \[\leq \frac{\eta^{2}\phi}{T}\sum_{\tau=0}^{T-1}\frac{1}{q_{1}-q_{2}} \left(\frac{q_{1}}{1-q_{1}}-\frac{q_{2}}{1-q_{2}}\right)\left[\frac{1}{M}\sum _{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|g_{\tau}-g_{r}^{m}\|^{2}\right]\] \[= \frac{\eta^{2}\phi}{(1-q_{1})(1-q_{2})}\frac{1}{T}\sum_{\tau=0}^ {T-1}\left[\frac{1}{M}\sum_{m=1}^{M}\mathbb{E}\|g_{\tau}-g_{\tau}^{m}\|^{2} \right].\]

Now, let us optimize the factor

\[\frac{\phi}{(1-q_{1})(1-q_{2})}=\frac{(1-p_{x})(1+\nicefrac{{1}}{{s}})(1-\beta )(1-p_{u})}{(1-(1-p_{x})(1+s))(1-(1-p_{u})\beta)}=\frac{(1-p_{x})(1+\nicefrac{ {1}}{{s}})}{1-(1-p_{x})(1+s)}.\frac{(1-\beta)(1-p_{u})}{1-(1-p_{u})\beta}\]by choosing optimal value for \(s\) introduced earlier. By the first order optimality condition, we find that the optimal value is \(s^{*}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{1-p_{x}}}-1\). Hence, the minimal value of the factor is

\[\frac{\phi}{(1-q_{1})(1-q_{2})} = \frac{1-p_{x}}{(1-\sqrt{1-p_{x}})^{2}}\cdot\frac{(1-\beta)(1-p_{u })}{1-(1-p_{u})\beta}\] \[= \frac{(1-p_{x})(1-\sqrt{1-p_{x}})^{2}}{(1-\sqrt{1-p_{x}})^{2}(1+ \sqrt{1-p_{x}})^{2}}\cdot\frac{(1-\beta)(1-p_{u})}{1-(1-p_{u})\beta}\] \[= \frac{(1-p_{x})(1+\sqrt{1-p_{x}})^{2}}{p_{x}^{2}}\cdot\frac{(1- \beta)(1-p_{u})}{1-(1-p_{u})\beta}\] \[\leq \frac{4(1-p_{x})}{p_{x}^{2}}\cdot\frac{(1-\beta)(1-p_{u})}{1-(1- p_{u})\beta}\stackrel{{\text{def}}}{{=}}\psi.\]

